definitions.definition: Of a system or protocol, such that it does not keep a persistent state between transactions.
examples: A stateless server treats each request independently.

definitions.definition: Without a state or nationality ; not subject to any state.
examples: UN Convention relating to the Status of Stateless Persons

definitions.definition: Neither believing in nor supporting the idea of nations .

main_definition: ( computer science ) Of a system or protocol, such that it does not keep a persistent state between transactions.
secondary_definitions: ( law ) Without a state or nationality ; not subject to any state.
( philosophy , politics ) Neither believing in nor supporting the idea of nations .
